I ran into an interesting problem when you delete a vanilla contaminated zone in runtime, some particles remain lying until the server restarts or relog.

The particles will spawn on the client's side and even if you move away from the deleted zone for several km and return back, the particles still lie in place.

It turns out that the particles does not have a "network bubble" like the rest of the entities and they always exist on the client.

This is a vanilla method of creating particles for the contaminated zone on the client

```cs
        //class EffectArea
    void OnParticleAllocation(ParticleManager pm, array<ParticleSource> particles)  
    {
        foreach (ParticleSource p : particles)
        {
            if (p.GetOwner() == this) // Safety, since it can be unrelated particles when done through event
                m_ToxicClouds.Insert(p);
        }
    }
```

I solved the problem with the remaining particles in this way

```cs

modded class EffectArea
{
    override void OnParticleAllocation(ParticleManager pm, array<ParticleSource> particles)
    {
        foreach (ParticleSource p : particles)
        {
            if (p.GetOwner() == this)
            {
                m_ToxicClouds.Insert(p);
            }
            else
            {
                p.Stop();
            }
        }
    }
}
```

